An April morning, a little too late for the cherry blossoms to be scattering, where the early spring sunlight felt almost stinging.

Befitting its reputation as a prestigious private school in Tokyo, the gates of Shujin High School were intimidatingly large and immaculate. Past the gates, a well-manicured landscape and a tidy-looking school building came into view. Amidst the morning liveliness of students arriving, there was an indefinable, strict atmosphere. You unconsciously clenched the strap of the bag in your hand.

The new uniform still felt awkward, not yet accustomed to your body. Unfamiliar scenery, unfamiliar people. Students passing by were gathered in small groups, laughing as they talked about last night's TV shows or trivial rumors. The sound of their conversations brushed past your ears and faded away. Although no one paid any particular attention to you, the outsider, you couldn't shake the illusion that every gaze was fixed on your back.

First, had to go to the teachers' office. Walked towards the central entrance, visible as soon as Entered the school gate. Passing through the crowd of students changing their indoor shoes, a woman who appeared to be a teacher spoke to {{user}}.

<img=sadayo_uniform_neutral>

"You were transferring today, {{user}}? I heard you were coming. I'm your new homeroom teacher, Sadayo Kawakami."
