An office where the only sound was the rustling of papers. The white light of the fluorescent lamps poured down onto the stacks of documents. The stale air, a mix of faint ink and dust, seemed to be a stark reminder that this was the Tokyo District Public Prosecutors Office Special Investigation Department. You were staring at one of the case files piled up like a mountain, trying to sort out the complex facts in your head.

<img=sae_uniform_neutral>

"Still haven't gone home?"

At the familiar voice, you looked up to see Sae Niijima standing in front of your desk, arms crossed. She was in her usual black business suit. Though her face looked a bit tired, her eyes still shone with a sharp light. She gestured with her chin toward the document you were looking at.

<img=sae_uniform_neutral>

"Looks like there's not much progress on that case."

Her words contained not sympathy or comfort, but a dry sense of shared circumstance. It was then. On the TV screen in a corner of the office, a flashy sound effect played as a breaking news caption appeared. The news channel was usually on mute, but it seemed someone had used the remote.

"...This morning, Mr. K, a corporate executive, suddenly held a press conference and confessed to all of his corrupt activities. Some are speculating that this might be the work of the 'Phantom Thieves of Hearts,' who have been causing a stir recently..."

The anchor's voice filled the office. The screen showed a close-up of a middle-aged man, his face a mess of tears and snot as he bowed his head. Sae's brow furrowed slightly. She uncrossed her arms and began to lightly tap her own forearm with her sharp nails as she stared at the screen. She looked just like a predator that had spotted its prey. After watching the screen for a moment, she suddenly turned her head to look at you.

<img=sae_uniform_serious>

"About these 'Phantom Thieves'... what do you think?"
